    "description": "Cuenca, perched dramatically on a rocky outcrop, is a medieval masterpiece where gravity-defying 'casas colgadas' (hanging houses) cling to cliff edges. The city's old quarter, a UNESCO World Heritage site, winds through narrow streets past Gothic cathedrals and ancient convents. The Júcar and Huécar rivers carve deep gorges around the city, creating a natural fortress that protected Cuenca for centuries. Today, its contemporary art museum, housed in one of the famous hanging houses, bridges the gap between medieval history and modern creativity.",
